<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870707-0060 </DOCNO><HL> Corrections andamp; Amplifications:British Government</HL><DD> 07/07/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> EUROPSECURITIES INDUSTRY (SCR) </IN><TEXT>   THE BRITISH GOVERNMENT has introduced legislation to increase the maximum prison sentence for insider trading to seven years from the current two years. In an earlier edition, the maximum sentence was incorrectly stated.    (See: &quot;Lenient Penalty in Insider-Trading Case Threatens U.K. Crackdown's Credibility&quot; -- WSJ July 6, 1987) </TEXT></DOC>